<div id="review_1752501330" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1752501330" />
    <a title="Julia Sapphire" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/39705390-julia-sapphire"><img alt="Julia Sapphire" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1642565162p2/39705390.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1752501330?book_show_action=true">Sep 08, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Julia Sapphire" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Julia Sapphire" href="/user/show/39705390-julia-sapphire">Julia Sapphire</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780811221689" href="/book/show/17574852-morphine">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39705390-julia-sapphire?shelf=mental-illness">mental-illness</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39705390-julia-sapphire?shelf=2016">2016</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1752501330" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3257717468226267998"><b> 3.25 out of 5 stars </b> <br/><br/><u> Trigger Warnings: Substance Abuse </u> <br/><br/>This was so different from what I usually read, and I quite liked it. Basically it&apos;s written by a Russian man which the story was translated to English. This story is about two doctors! The man we follow who moves to a small town to work at a clinic. As he is there working he gets a letter from a friend in med school, asking him for help for he has fallen ill. The doctor is planning on helping out his friend, then he arrives in his clinic</span>
  <span id="freeText3257717468226267998" style="display:none"><b> 3.25 out of 5 stars </b> <br /><br /><u> Trigger Warnings: Substance Abuse </u> <br /><br />This was so different from what I usually read, and I quite liked it. Basically it's written by a Russian man which the story was translated to English. This story is about two doctors! The man we follow who moves to a small town to work at a clinic. As he is there working he gets a letter from a friend in med school, asking him for help for he has fallen ill. The doctor is planning on helping out his friend, then he arrives in his clinic near death. Before he passes away, he gives the doctor a journal about his medical struggles. Him dealing with his addiction of Morphine. <br /><br />I thought the way addiction was portrayed and told was so great. It made it sound so real and that not only does your mind want it but your body grows to need it too. This was very short but really got my thinking, it was quite thought provoking. <br /><br /><i> <b> "Clever people have been pointing out for a long time that happiness is like good health: when it's there, you don't notice it. But years have passed, oh, how do you remember it!" </b></i> </span>
  <a data-text-id="3257717468226267998" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


