<div id="review_4048237577" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4048237577" />
    <a title="Destini " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/70002134-destini"><img alt="Destini " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1624846834p2/70002134.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4048237577?book_show_action=true">Jun 08, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Destini " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Destini " href="/user/show/70002134-destini">Destini </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/70002134-destini?shelf=russian-literature">russian-literature</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4048237577" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16734737148240439584"><p> I bought <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/4531917.Morphine' title='Morphine by Mikhail Bulgakov' rel='nofollow noopener'>Morphine</a> on a whim and I loved it! I&apos;ll keep my review brief because it is a short story. The story is about a doctor who receives his colleague&apos;s (Dr.Polyakov) journal. Throughout the journal, the whole tragedy of Dr. Polyakov&apos;s addiction is notated. It seems seems unoriginal, but Bulgakov&apos;s writing sets this story apart. I don&apos;t want to give too much away because it is so short; but I am now more and more addicted to Russian literature. I&apos;ll be starting &quot;Heart of a Dog&quot; and &quot;Master a</p></span>
  <span id="freeText16734737148240439584" style="display:none"><p> I bought <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/4531917.Morphine" title="Morphine by Mikhail Bulgakov" rel="nofollow noopener">Morphine</a> on a whim and I loved it! I'll keep my review brief because it is a short story. The story is about a doctor who receives his colleague's (Dr.Polyakov) journal. Throughout the journal, the whole tragedy of Dr. Polyakov's addiction is notated. It seems seems unoriginal, but Bulgakov's writing sets this story apart. I don't want to give too much away because it is so short; but I am now more and more addicted to Russian literature. I'll be starting "Heart of a Dog" and "Master and Margarita" soon. </p><br /><br /><a href="https://www.instagram.com/bookswithbonnets/" rel="nofollow noopener">Instagram</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="16734737148240439584" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


