<span id="freeTextContainer16272821345260307725"><i> Morphine hydrochloricum is, indeed, a formidable thing. The habit for it forms very quickly. But a little habit isn&apos;t morphine addiction.is it..? </i><br/>Mikhail Bulgakov&apos;s morphine is a smaller but realistic depiction of a young doctor&apos;s journey on spiraling down the path of addiction. This one is medically accurate thanks to Mikhail&apos;s profession. The story is part of a notebook that is given with a suicide letter to treat as a medical journal. I like this one more than m &amp; m. Doctor&apos;s descent to addi</span>
  <span id="freeText16272821345260307725" style="display:none"><i> Morphine hydrochloricum is, indeed, a formidable thing. The habit for it forms very quickly. But a little habit isn't morphine addiction.is it..? </i><br />Mikhail Bulgakov's morphine is a smaller but realistic depiction of a young doctor's journey on spiraling down the path of addiction. This one is medically accurate thanks to Mikhail's profession. The story is part of a notebook that is given with a suicide letter to treat as a medical journal. I like this one more than m &amp; m. Doctor's descent to addiction as the power of the doses increases with parts of the water. When one pain starts to ease then another problem starts to occur like a hallucination.<br /><i>In short, the man is gone. He's switched off. it's a corpse that moves, yearns, suffers. He wants nothing, thinks about nothing but morphine. Morphine! </i><br /><br /> Bulgakov showed the dark side of the white powder where the world starts to treat it as a miracle.</span>
