<div id="review_1362761894" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1362761894" />
    <a title="Alor Deng" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3096095-alor-deng"><img alt="Alor Deng" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1417102582p2/3096095.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1362761894?book_show_action=true">Aug 13, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Alor Deng" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Alor Deng" href="/user/show/3096095-alor-deng">Alor Deng</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3096095-alor-deng?shelf=short-stories">short-stories</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3096095-alor-deng?shelf=russian">russian</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1362761894" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1113530264824097010">Bulgakov is a fantastic writer. He writes here of the slow descent of a young and intelligent doctor into addiction. The writing is such that one has to question whether Bulgakov himself was an addict- such is the psychological insight he presents. The most intriguing part is how the doctor first gets addicted. It is so innocuous, there is absolutely no presentiment that warns him of addiction. This could serve as a cautionary tale to any person in society. The best way to prevent addiction is t</span>
  <span id="freeText1113530264824097010" style="display:none">Bulgakov is a fantastic writer. He writes here of the slow descent of a young and intelligent doctor into addiction. The writing is such that one has to question whether Bulgakov himself was an addict- such is the psychological insight he presents. The most intriguing part is how the doctor first gets addicted. It is so innocuous, there is absolutely no presentiment that warns him of addiction. This could serve as a cautionary tale to any person in society. The best way to prevent addiction is to not try it in the first place.</span>
