    <a title="Stone Sliminess" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/44189422-stone-sliminess"><img alt="Stone Sliminess" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1641281269p2/44189422.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2226094939?book_show_action=true">Dec 25, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Stone Sliminess" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Stone Sliminess" href="/user/show/44189422-stone-sliminess">Stone Sliminess</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780811221689" href="/book/show/17574852-morphine">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2226094939" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12378654787779427408">I&apos;ve never been addicted to anything really, let alone morphine, so I&apos;m not able to understand this book, perhaps as deeply as some. However, I did enjoy this little book. It takes like half an hour to read so I can easily recommend this to anyone and especially anyone who has struggled with addiction or is still struggling. If anyone has any experience with addiction (especially to drugs and especially morphine), and has read this, let me know how well Bulgakov has captured these emotions. </span>
  <span id="freeText12378654787779427408" style="display:none">I've never been addicted to anything really, let alone morphine, so I'm not able to understand this book, perhaps as deeply as some. However, I did enjoy this little book. It takes like half an hour to read so I can easily recommend this to anyone and especially anyone who has struggled with addiction or is still struggling. If anyone has any experience with addiction (especially to drugs and especially morphine), and has read this, let me know how well Bulgakov has captured these emotions. </span>
  <a data-text-id="12378654787779427408" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
